        "title": "SEC Unveils Bold Climate Disclosure Rules, Sparking Industry Debate and Legal Challenges",
        "summary": "The SEC has proposed new climate disclosure regulations that would require public companies to report climate-related risks and emissions in their annual filings. These rules could significantly increase compliance costs for Fortune 500 companies, with a phased timeline for implementation beginning in 2024.",
